<HEADLINE> Weis Sets Year's Best Hammer Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Germany's European Cup champion Heinz
 Weis set the world best mark this year with 83.04 meters in the
men's hammer at an international athletics meeting in Frankfurt,
Germany, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old beat the previous best mark 81.64 set by
Italy's Enrico Sgrulletti earlier this year.  
</P>
