<HEADLINE> CPPCC Standing Committee Meeting Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Committee, China's top political advisory body, ended
its 21st session here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
and chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, presided over the
closing meeting and made a speech.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC National Committee Vice-chairman Ye Xuanping said in his
summary of the three-day session that the meeting concentrated on
the study of Deng Xiaoping's theory on the people's political
consultative system, and reviewed the work of the CPPCC Eighth
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth National Committee has improved itself, made
outstanding achievements in many aspects, and gained some good
experience and practice over the past few years, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will be back to the motherland in less than two days,
he added. He also urged his colleagues in the CPPCC to celebrate
the great event and fulfill their duties in the last year of the
Eighth National Committee's term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
