<HEADLINE> Ghana, Ireland, Argentina and Uruguay Enter Top Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LAMPUR, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Ghana, Ireland, Argentina and
Uruguay advanced to the semifinals of the World Youth Football
Championship in Malaysia on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ghana beat Japan 2-1 in the quarterfinals at the Larkin Stadium
in Johor Baharu, southern Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Ireland advanced to the semifinals by defeating Spain 1-0 at
Shah Alam Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Ireland's winning goal was scored by Trevor Molly who converted
a penalty kick in the 50th minute.
</P>
<P>
Argentina beat Brazil 2-0 in the quarterfinals at the Sarawak
Stadium in Kuching, East Malaysia, today.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay defeated France 7-6 after a penalty shoot-out in the
quarterfinals at Shah Alam Stadium this evening. Both teams were
tied 1-1 after extra time.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals to be held on July 2, Ghana will meet Uruguay
while Ireland will take on Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
