<HEADLINE> U.S. Conducts Aerial Reconnaissances on DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States since June
first had sent various types of stragetic and tactical scout
planes to conduct over 150 aerial reconnaissances on the
territorial air of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea
(DPRK), the Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) reported today by
quoting the DPRK armed forces.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that U.S. "U 9990 2" stragetic scout planes,
"E 9990 3" early warning planes, "RC 9990 135", "RF 9990 4C" and
other types of tactical planes and electronic helicopters had
conducted aerial reconnaissances, aerial photography and
electronic spying above DPRK's Teok Jeok island, Chun Chon city,
Yang Yang city and even the military demarcation line.
</P>
<P>
According to KCNA reports, the U.S. troops' "RC 9990 12",
"RF 9990 4C", "P 9990 3" and "EH 9990 60" tactical and electronic
planes had made more frequent spying activites over DPRK
territorial air day and night. On June 22, 24 and 27, the
U.S. airforce flied five, seven and eight sorites to conduct
aerial spying on DPRK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
