<HEADLINE> 800 Guests to Attend Hong Kong Handover Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 800 representatives and
guests from 40 countries and regions, and 30 international and
regional organizations will attend the Hong Kong handover ceremony
at midnight on June 30.
</P>
<P>
The guests will attend the ceremony to be held at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center Extention to witness this
historic event.
</P>
<P>
Among the guests will be Colombian President Ernesto Samper,
who is also chairman of the Non-Alignment Movement, President of
Peru's Council of Ministers Alberto Pandolfi Arbulu, President of
the French Senate Rene Monory, German Vice Chancellor and Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel, New Zealand Vice Prime Minister and Finance
Minister Winston Peters, U.S. Secretary of State Madaleine
Albright, Japanese Foreign Minister Iketa Yukihiko and Russian
Foreign Minister Evgeny Primakov, Portugal Foreign Minister Jaime
Gama and Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer, as well as
representatives of a number of countries and Macao Governor Vasco
Josquim Rocha Vieira.
</P>
<P>
The guests will also include more than 60 representatives of
international and regional organizations, including U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan, and representatives of the U.N. Food
and Agriculture Organization, the World Health Organization, the
World Trade Organization, the World Bank, the International
Monetary Fund, the Arab League, the Organization of African Unity,
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations and the European
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Alao present at the ceremony will be former Tanzanian President
Julius Nyerere, former Mexican President Lius Echeverria Alvarez,
former British prime mnisters Edward Heath and Margarat Thatcher,
former Australian prime ministers John Malcolm Fraser and Robert
James Lee Hawke, former Japanese Prime Minister Murayama Tomiichi,
and .
</P>
<P>
Also atternding the ceremony will be consuls-general of more
than 90 countries in Hong Kong, representatives of the Hong Kong
offices of some international organizations, and leaders of
economic, educational, cultural and social organizations and
non-governmental organizations of various countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, nearly 300 representatives of overseas Chinese and
 foreigners of Chinese origin from 33 countries and regions, as
well as dozens of people from Taiwan will also attend the
ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
