<HEADLINE> Iraqi Parliamentary Delegation Leaves for Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 29 (Xinhua) -- An Iraqi National Assembly
delegation led by Chairman Saadoun Hammadi left here today for
Moscow on an official visit to Russia, according to the Iraqi News
Agency (INA).
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the INA before his departure, Hammadi said
the delegation will hold talks with Russian officials on the means
of enhancing bilateral cooperation in health, economic and
political aspects.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will brief Russian officials on the latest
developments in the relations between Iraq and the U.N., and the
attempts of the U.S. to hold back and delay the approval of Iraq's
contracts with foreign companies under its oil-for-food deal with
the UN, Hammadi said,
</P>
<P>
He added that during the visit, the delegation will conclude a
cooperation agreement with the Russian Federation Council (Upper
House) and State Duma (Lower House) to improve relations between
the two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
