<HEADLINE> Roundup: Macao Celebrates HK's Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao residents today staged
artistic performances and exhibitions, planted trees and held
races to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the motherland,
which was slated for July 1.
</P>
<P>
Celebration activities in Macao have increased remarkably over
the past weeks as the time draws near July 1. Almost all
grassroots organizations and bodies of different industries have
held parties, discussions, singing and dancing galas and other
forms of activities to mark the historic event.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Women's Federation staged a performance of
celebration early in the morning today. More than 100 women and
children sang, danced, recited poems, chorused and staged a
fashion show.
</P>
<P>
"The performance is to express their love for their motherland
and their happiness with the return of Hong Kong to China," said
Lo Pak Sam, president of the federation. "It is a big event not
only for Hong Kongers, but also for us in Macao."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large exhibition organized by 14 local art
organizations began here today. Organizers said that the 121
pieces of calligraphic works and paintings on display eulogize the
concept of "one country, two systems" and the Basic Law of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to express our heartfelt wishes for the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) through our paintings," said
Luk Cheung, head of the organizing committee in an opening address
at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the exhibition began, thousands of Macao workers,
students and ordinary citizens started a race in the name of
celebration. Wearing T-shirts marked with "Celebrate Hong Kong's
Return," they ran about 2,000 meters in the street.
</P>
<P>
Chinese civil servants planted trees today, while many sports
and education organizations planned to stage celebration galas
tonight.
</P>
<P>
Major buildings and streets in Macao have been lit up at night
and decorated with red lanterns and banners. The celebration is
expected to come to a climax on June 30 and July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
