<HEADLINE> Uruguay Beats France in Penalty Shoot-out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay advanced to the
semi-finals of the world youth football championship after beating
France 7-6 in a penalty shoot-out here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
France opened the scoring through David Trezeguet's 26th minute
goal, but Nicolas Olivera tied the score in the 67th minute.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's goalkeeper Gustavo Munua saved a penalty from Nicolas
Anelka to take his team into the last four, where they will meet
either Ghana or Japan, who play later on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
France began the shoot-out badly when goalkeeper Mickael
Landreau's kick was saved by Munua. But Uruguay's second shot by
Walter Coelho then hit the bar.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's successful shooters were Marcelo Zalayeta, Mario
Regueiro, Pablo Garcia, Nicolas Olivera, Christian Callejas,
Martin Fernandez and Carlos Diaz.
</P>
<P>
For France, Trezeguet, Kodjo Afanou, Medhi Leroy, Cedric
Mouret, Jean Joures and Mikael Silvestre scored.
</P>
<P>
The defeat marred a personal triumph for Trezeguet, who scored
his sixth goal to take second place behind Brazil's Adailton
Martins (10) in the list of goal scorers.
</P>
<P>
Both players, however, will not have a chance to increase the
tally as Brazil crashed to a 2-0 defeat against defending
champions Argentina earlier on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
