<HEADLINE> New Airport Opens to Flights in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Lukou Airport in Nanjing, capital
of east China's Jiangsu Province, opened for service today,
complete with state-of-the-art telecommunications, navigation, and
air control equipment capable of handling Boeing 747s.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and vice-premier of the
State Council, attended the opening ceremony here today.
</P>
<P>
The airport, located 35 kilometers from downtown Nanjing, is
jointly funded by the local governments of Jiangsu Province and
Nanjing City, and the Civil Aviation Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of the first-phase project, the airport is
designed to have an annual capacity of handling 69,600 flights, or
a passenger volume of 8.64 million and a cargo volume of 119,800
tons.
</P>
<P>
The terminal building has an area of 92,000 square meters.
</P>
</TEXT>
