<HEADLINE> Israel's Anti-Muslim Acts Condemned by Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait today strongly
condemned the anti-Islam acts carried out Saturday by Jewish
settlers in Hebron and called on the international community to
pressure the Jewish state to stop these acts.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Minister of State for Cabinet Affairs Abdul Aziz
Dakhil Al-Dakhil said in a statement after a weekly cabinet
session that "Kuwait strongly condemns anti-Islam provocation and
calls on the international community to pressure the Israeli
authorities to stop these humiliating acts which targeted Islam
and Prophet Mohammed."
</P>
<P>
Jewish settlers Saturday pasted anti-Muslim posters on about
20 storefronts near a Jewish settlement in the West Bank city of
Hebron tarnishing Prophet Mohammed as a pig.
</P>
<P>
The anti-Muslim acts led to Palestinian demonstrations in which
clashes flared between the protesters and Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Reports said at least two Palestinians were wounded by
Israeli soldiers' rubber bullets in the clashes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
