<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Five-time defending champions Japan
beat Thailand in the final to win the Asian Pacific Cup men's
volleyball tournament for a sixth year running in Fukuoka, Japan,
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese spikers, who are made up of members of their World
Student Games team, scored a 15-7, 9-15, 16-14, 15-9 victory
to end the six-team tournament with five consecutive wins.
</P>
