<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Newspapers Splash Hong Kong Stories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China has
become the major issue in the Bulgarian press in recent days with
major papers splashing whole-page stories about the event.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's most widely circulated daily newspaper, 24 Chasa
(Hours), today devoted a whole page to the history of Hong Kong
with the headline: "Britain: Farewell, Hong Kong!"
</P>
<P>
At midnight on June 30, Britain will lower its flag in Hong
Kong and the Chinese flag will fly over the richest island in the
world, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The "one Country, two Systems" concept put forward by late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping laid the foundation for Hong Kong's
smooth return to China, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Labor newspaper said Friday that the return of Hong Kong to
China after more than 150 years of British colonial rule is surely
the biggest and most brilliant event.
</P>
<P>
The paper noted that the agreement signed between Britain and
China on the question of Hong Kong in 1984 was one of the greatest
achievements of Deng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
