<HEADLINE> Chinese Americans in California Celebrate HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 29 (Xinhua) -- More than 20,000 Chinese
Americans gathered in a college stadium here today to celebrate
the return of Hong Kong to China at midnight on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The largest ever Chinese gathering in the United States, named
"Welcome Home Hong Kong Spectacular", was sponsored jointly by
more than 100 associations and guilds in southern California to
mark the end of more than 150 years of British colonial rule of
the island.
</P>
<P>
A congratulatory message to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Premier Li Peng was read out at the rally, followed by another to
the chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, Tung Chee-hwa, and his fellow six million residents of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Consul General of the Chinese Consulate General in Los Angeles,
Feng Shusen, and the city's mayor, Richard Riordan, spoke at the
meeting, which attracted hundreds of local Americans.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1997 white pigeons were freed, followed by a parade
of floral floats and marching bands representing 80 organizations.
</P>
<P>
A half hour of colorful fireworks lightened the sky as the
ceremony entered the stage of evening party, which included
symphonic music, chorus, dances, martial arts and the performance
of a local concert band. 
</P>
</TEXT>
