<HEADLINE> Philippines Makes Visa Arrangement for HK Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will allow
residents of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region to stay
without visa requirement for a week after Hong Kong returns to
China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by Philippine President Fidel Ramos in
a statement issued on the eve of the handover.
</P>
<P>
"As a signal expression of our confidence in the bright future
of Hong Kong," Ramos said, the Philippines will allow holders of
the Hong Kong Special Administration Region passports to enter the
Philippines without need of visas for a maximum period of seven
days.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed the heartfelt greetings and felicitations of the
Filipino people and the Philippine government to the people of
Hong Kong for the territory's return to its motherland.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said that the economic vitality and political stability
of Hong Kong is of critical importance to the continued
prosperity of the Asia-Pacific region, including those of the
Philippines, and to a vibrant global trade in general.
</P>
<P>
He said he is hopeful that the 1984 Sino-British joint
declaration on the question of Hong Kong and the "one country, two
systems" principle will be implemented faithfully.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that the Philippines' close and
fruitful partnership with Hong Kong will continue to flourish
in trade, investments and people-to-people exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
