<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Perks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Putting a brake to its
continuous decline, India's annual rate of inflation went up
marginally by 0.02 percentage points to close the week ended June
14 at 5.85 percent, the Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The inflation has witnessing a declining trend due to fall in
prices of "primary articles" in the last three months, especially
vegetables.
</P>
<P>
The rate of inflation during the corresponding week last year
was 4.40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the official wholesale price index for "all
commodities" (base 1981-82=100) recorded a 0.2 percent rise to
323.8 during the week under review as against 323.2 in the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
The reference week witnessed an increase in prices of
commodities such as tea and fodder.  
