<HEADLINE> 5 Tamil Rebels killed In North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- At least five Tamil rebels were
killed Saturday evening when they attacked a government patrol in
the Northern province of Sri Lanka, according to military sources
here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said government troops on patrol at Nedurkerny
confronted a group of Tamil rebels and killed at least five of
them, while one soldier was injured during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired mortars at the troops and the troops
retaliated with artillery and mortars.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the Sri
Lankan government for a separate state in the north and east of
the country since 1983. 
</P>
