<HEADLINE> Rainstorm Hits Northern Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 28 (Xinhua) -- At least two people have died and
another one missing in a rainstorm that has hit Northern Italy for
the last few days.
</P>
<P>
Continuous heavy rains in the north caused landslides and
paralyzed part of railway and road transportation. Some rivers
and lakes have been rising and houses been toppled down.
</P>
<P>
A state of emergency was declared in the worst-hit province of
Trento today.
</P>
<P>
Showers were still reported early today in the region although
occasional sunshines were seen for the first time in several
days. 
