<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: "One country, two systems" Concept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The concept of "one Country, two
systems" is a great innovation developed by the late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping, said Mirza Gholam Hafiz, President of the
Bangladesh-China Friendship Association (BCFA).
</P>
<P>
During a recent interview with Xinhua, Mr. Hafiz, now
77-year-old, recalled his long-time friendship with China. "When
the new China was founded in 1949, my friends and I, still young
at that time, were much excited and held a special function to
celebrate the historical event."
</P>
<P>
Having been the president of the BCFA for more than 30 years,
Mr. Hafiz contributed a great deal to the Sino-Bangladesh
friendship. In 1994, he was awarded the title of the "Friendship
Ambassador" by the Chinese People's Association for Friendship
with Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
"As a politician, I have to say the concept of "one country,
two systems" is a new development in International Political
Science," said Hafiz, who served as the Speaker of Bangladeshi
parliament from 1975 to 1983 and Minister of Law in early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
In his view, this workable system will set a good example for
other regions facing similar problems.
</P>
<P>
Under the system, Hong Kong, after July 1, will be governed by
a government made up of local people, enjoy a high degree of
autonomy and have its own customs and tax system. "This will
guarantee Hong Kong to continue as a free port and a major
international finance and trade center." he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in addition to Hong Kong, Macao will also return
to China in a few years under the concept of "one country, two
systems". This has testified to the feasibility and practicality
of the concept which also opened the door for resolving the Taiwan
issue.
</P>
<P>
Hafiz, who will attend the grand ceremony marking the return of
Hong Kong to China, said: "Hong Kong's return is a very happy
development in modern world history." 
</P>
</TEXT>
