<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Have More Business Opportunities After Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is bound to have more
business opportunities in China's interior areas as well as in the
global marketplace with Hong Kong as the headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made by Dr. Victor Fung, chairman of the Hong
Kong Trade Development Council (HKTDC) today.
</P>
<P>
"China's opening to the outside world more than a dozen years
ago provided an opportunity for Hong Kong and its return to the
motherland represents a new opportunity," said Dr. Fung.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Fung said Hong Kong can enhance its cooperative ties with
the rest of China in such fields as product design, packaging,
infrastructure construction as the city boasts a very developed
service industry.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Fung said HKTDC can help promote products made in the
interior areas on the world market by making use of its global
market network.
</P>
<P>
The service trade has made up 80 percent of the product value
and the number of employees also constituted 80 percent of the
total employment in Hong Kong. Not long ago, the Trade Council
announced that it will allocate 40 million HK dollars to
strengthen Hong Kong's status as a the center of service in the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong is the world's fourth source of direct foreign
investment, its direct investment outside the region reached 25
billion US dollars last year, and Fung said that his council will
help encourage and organize more overseas business people to
invest in China in the years ahead.
More than 50,000 Hong Kong-funded firms have been established in
China's interior areas and more enterprises will follow suit, he
estimated.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that trade with the interior areas accounts
for more than one third of Hong Kong's 400 billion US dollar-worth
annual external trade volume.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1966, the TDC has been engaged in exploring Hong
Kong's trade with the rest of the world. The council has so far
established 51 offices in 34 countries and regions worldwide, 11
of which are in interior areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
