<HEADLINE> Malaysian Acting PM Optimistic about HK's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Acting Prime
Minister Ibrahim Anwar is optimistic about the future of Hong
Kong, believing that Hong Kong will remain prosperous after its
return to China.
</P>
<P>
Anwar expressed his view to reporters after chairing the
meeting of the Penang State Liaison Committee of the ruling
United Malays National Organization (UMNO) in Penang, northwest
Malaysia, yesterday, according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
The Acting Prime Minister said that after the return of Hong
Kong to China, Malaysia's consistent policy toward businessmen and
visitors would continue.
</P>
<P>
He said "we do not want our tourism affected."
</P>
<P>
Anwar said his government would issue instructions to its
consulate in Hong Kong to speed up the visa approval process to
facilitate Hong Kong residents' travel to Malaysia.  
</P>
