<HEADLINE> Popov Wins at Santa Clara Invitational Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Alexander Popov,
double Olympic gold medalist in the men's 50-meter and 100-meter,
chalked up a title in the 50-meter freestyle on Saturday at the
Santa Clara Invitational Swimming tournament.
</P>
<P>
The world record holder touched the pad with a winning time of
22.78 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The race was Popov's first since being stabbed on a Moscow
street by a water melon seller last August.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Nathan Rickard was second in 23.19 seconds,
followed by American Neil Walker who finished third at 23.27
seconds. 
</P>
