<HEADLINE> Chilean Copper Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Chile produced 1.061 million tons
of copper during the first four months of the year, a more than 10
percent increase over the same period of 1996, according to the
Chilean Copper Commission (Cochilco).
</P>
<P>
The average price of the metal during the first five months of
the year was about 1.1 U.S. dollars a pound, against the price of
1.03 dollars a pound last year.
</P>
<P>
Cochilco experts estimated copper price will drop during the
second half of the year, because of a rise in world output of
copper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
