<HEADLINE> Mexico Takes Bronze at Copa America Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Luis Hernandez scored the only
goal of the match nine minutes before the final whistle to help
Mexico gain a 1-0 win over Peru on Saturday and a bronze medal at
the Copa America soccer tournament in Oruro, Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
It was Hernandez's sixth goal at the current tournament, two
goals more than Brazilian international Ronaldo, 20, world
footballer in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Mexico dominated most of the time while their efforts finally
paid off through Hernandez, who converted on a header off a cross
from teammate Gilberto Jimenez.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will clash with Bolivia to vie for the title of the
tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Mexico, which played as an invited guest from
CONCACAF, its second medal finish in three outings in the South
American Championship. It lost in the final in 1993 to Argentina
and was eliminated in the quarterfinals in 1995 by the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
