<HEADLINE> Economic Cooperation Between Mainland and Hong Kong News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Following are the news in brief on
economic cooperation between Chinese provinces and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan-Hong Kong Sign Largest Power Project Agreement
</P>
<P>
An agreement on a thermal power project jointly funded by
Sichuan and Hong Kong was signed recently.
</P>
<P>
The two 142,000-kilowatt generating units will cost 2.5 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Top Investor in Tianjin Bonded Zone
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is now the leader in a bonded zone in north China's
Tianjin Municipality in investment and number of enterprises with
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has registered 1,270 enterprises with a combined
investment of 1.2 billion US dollars in the zone, according to
local sources.
</P>
<P>
HK Accounts For 60 percent of Hunan's Overseas Investment
</P>
<P>
Investment from Hong Kong accounted for 58.2 percent of the
overseas investment in central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
There are 2,742 Hong Kong-backed companies registered in the
province. Of the 2.39 billion US dollars contractual investment
from Hong Kong, more than one billion is being used.
</P>
<P>
Fujian-Hong Kong Financial Ties
</P>
<P>
Fujian Province on the southeast coast of China plans to
further develop financial cooperation with Hong Kong after the
return.
</P>
<P>
The province will tap Hong Kong's capital market for its own
economic growth while gradually opening its financial market in
securities and fund-raising. 
</P>
</TEXT>
