<DOCNO> XIE19970629.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Powerful China Basic Guarantee for HK's Return: Nyerere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Former Tanzanian President
Julius Kambarage Nyerere said here today that a powerful China is
the basic guarantee for the smooth return of Hong Kong to its
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The long-cherished wish to bring Hong Kong back into the
embrace of China is realized only today when China has developed
and become powerful, Nyerere said before leaving for Hong Kong to
view the hand-over ceremony to be held on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, 75, one of the founders of the Sino-Tanzanian
friendship, has conducted 13 visits to China.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Nyerere said that Hong
Kong will be more prosperous after its return to China, and its
position as a world financial and trade center will be further
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
He added that the basic policies of "one country, two systems",
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree
autonomy" will be the key to Hong Kong's further development and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere spoke highly of the concept of "one country, two
systems", which was put forward by Late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping for solving the questions of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said the settlement of the Hong Kong question has proved the
correctness of Deng's concept and this concept will promote the
smooth settlement of the Taiwan question.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere stressed that for any country or any region, peace and
stability are the only way to gain economic and social
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970629.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
