<HEADLINE> Hide Wins WBO Heavyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Herbie of Britain Hide scored a
second-round knockout win over American veteran Tony Tucker on
Saturday to win the vacant World Boxing Organisation heavyweight
title in Norwich of England.
</P>
<P>
Hide, 25, who previously held the title in 1995, lifted his
record to 29 wins and one loss -- against Riddick Bowe -- while
the 38-year-old Tucker's record dropped to 54-6.
</P>
<P>
Hide showed no sign of ring rust despite having fought only
twice since losing his WBO crown to Bowe in Las Vegas 27 months
ago.
</P>
<P>
In a support bout, England's Jonathan Thaxton scored a
second-round knockout win over German-based Armenian Gagik
Khachatrian in a bout billed for both the WBO and IBF
Inter-Continental light-welterweight titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
