<HEADLINE> 20,000 Tins of Fake Esso Lubricant Seized in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Commercial and industrial
administrative offices of Nanning, capital of the Guangxi
Autonomous Region in southwest China, have seized more than 20,000
tins of fake Esso lubricating oil since last November in
cooperation with Esso's Hong Kong branch.
</P>
<P>
According to a spokesman of the Nanning Industrial and
Commercial Administration, the city has shut down 18 stores
selling fake Esso lubricants, and one underground lubricant plant
involved in producing the fake lubricant.
</P>
<P>
He said that close coordination with representatives of Esso
Hong Kong, Ltd., had allowed Nanning to conduct several checks on
local lubricant markets, thereby helping protect Esso's business
in the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
