<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Return to China Celebrated in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Institute For the Promotion of
Euro-Chinese Relations in Greece today held a reception to mark
the return of Hong Kong to China on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in his opening speech, Stavros Nikolakopoulos,
president of the organization, congratulated China for regaining
sovereignty over Hong Kong through peaceful means, saying that the
concept of "one country, two systems" proposed by the late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping showed a great wisdom.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the confidence that with a high autonomy promised
by the concept, Hong Kong, as a significant world financial and
business center, will be even more prosperous after its return.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, Yang Guangsheng, Chinese Ambassador to
Greece, also said that Hong Kong's return to China was an event of
historic importance, putting an end to the more than 150-year
colonial rule by Britain.
</P>
<P>
The peaceful settlement of the Hong Kong issue was a good
example in resolving issues left over from the past, he said,
adding that this would make considerably contributions to peace,
stability and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 people from all walks of life in Greece attended the
reception tonight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
