<HEADLINE> Two Killed in California Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A plane crashed Saturday
morning on the southwest side of Box Springs Mountain in Riverside
County, California, killing two male passengers.
</P>
<P>
Residents reported hearing a low-flying plane and a loud crash
just before 7:30 a.m. local time near the Box Springs Mountain
Park, about 63 miles east of Los Angeles, The United Press
International reported.
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies responding to reports were led to the badly
mangled plane by two mountain bikers, at which time the two
victims were discovered. It was not clear whether anyone else was
killed because authorities have not gone through all the wreckage.
</P>
<P>
Investigators from the Federal Aviation Administration and the
National Transportation Safety Board said they may have the
wreckage airlifted from the mountain side to an area where it can
be examined more thoroughly.
</P>
<P>
The area was reportedly blanketed by a thick layer of fog
around the time of the crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
